						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary stone above the sculpture of a swan, lying near Kalamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record states that it is the <hi rend="italic">dharma</hi> of the Two Hundred and the <hi rend="italic">Ūrōḍeya,</hi> caused to be made by Sōvarāsi of Kōḷivāḍa. The characters are of about 12th century A.D.</p>						

